Chuikov joined the Red Army in 1919. He fought in the Russian Civil War and the Polish-Soviet War. He was a participant in the Russian invasion of Poland in 1939.

input: Write a short biography of Terrence Romeo.
output:
Terrence Romeo is a Filipino professional basketball player for the GlobalPort Batang Pier of the Philippine Basketball Association (PBA). He was drafted 1st overall by the Batang Pier in the 2013 PBA draft.

## Early life

Romeo was born in Manila, Philippines. He is the son of former PBA player and coach, Romeo Mamaril.

## College career

Romeo played for the University of the East Red Warriors in the UAAP. He was named Rookie of the Year in his first year in the league. He was also named MVP in his sophomore year.

## Professional career

### 2013 PBA draft

Romeo was drafted 1st overall by the GlobalPort Batang Pier in the 2013 PBA draft.

### GlobalPort Batang Pier

Romeo made his debut in the PBA on October 20, 2013, in a game against the Talk 'N Text Tropang Texters. He scored 11 points in his debut game.

LONDON: HENRY COLBURN, PUBLISHER, GREAT MARLBOROUGH STREET.

1832.

The following pages are intended to give a short and simple account of the life of Richard Burton, the celebrated traveller and orientalist.

The work is not intended to be a complete biography, but merely a sketch of the principal events in the life of the traveller.

H. H. B.

Muhammad Alhamid (1859-1920) was a Moroccan writer and journalist.

He returned to Morocco in 1881 and worked as a journalist for the French newspaper Le Petit Marocain. He was also a member of the Moroccan delegation to the Paris Peace Conference in 1919.

He died in 1920 in Marrakesh.

Krystyna Szczepańska

Données clésAuteur

## Biographie

Krystyna Szczepańska est née le 1er janvier 1923 à Varsovie. Elle est la fille de Józef Szczepański, un écrivain et journaliste, et de Maria Szczepańska, une écrivaine. Elle a deux frères, Józef et Andrzej.

Elle a étudié à l'École de commerce de Varsovie. Elle a travaillé comme comptable et a été membre de l'Union des écrivains polonais.

Elle a écrit des romans, des nouvelles et des pièces de théâtre.

Elle est décédée le 14 janvier 2011 à Varsovie.
